{
  "text": "\u2022 Why and how a weakly supervised model can outperform the weak labeler? \u2022 What properties should the weakly supervised models have to perform effectively? Our recent work [CITATION_1] studies weak supervision for information retrieval with a focus on learning to rank and models weak supervision as a noisy channel that introduces some noise to the true labels. Motivated by the symmetry condition defined for classification [CITATION_2] , we define symmetric ranking loss function as follows. where c is a constant number and Y is a finite and discrete output space. In case of binary relevance judgments, the output space Y is {0, 1} n for a rank list of n items.",
  "citation_candidates": [
